      • getTileImage

        public javafx.scene.image.Image getTileImage()
        This method returns the path to and thus the image belonging to the tile it is applied to. In case there is more than one image for one tileType, the method differentiates between those different elements in taking account of further tile attributes (as can be seen within the if-else-clauses). Which additional tile attributes were chosen depend on the tile classes - the attributes that differ from the parent class tile are the only ones that are not null in the subclasses and are hence the only viable option to differentiate between different objects of the same subclass
        Returns:
